Description: Part of a comprehensive system, this Geberit FlowFit 40mm equal tee is made of polyphenylsulfone (PPSU) and fitted with press-fit connections. Developed with the input of the plumbers who will use it, the innovative FlowFit system ensures always-right installation, for a simpler job on-site with no need for deburring and calibration when cutting to length and the ability to laterally press and rotate for convenient and reliable pressing in difficult spots with no risk of contortion. This system is compatible with both cold and hot potable water, cooling and heating water with or without antifreeze agent and with service water and process water. It can also be used in treated water, rainwater with a pH value of <gt/>6, seawater and extinguishing water (wet, wet/dry or dry). It is also suitable for chemicals and technical liquids, compressed air (oil purity class 0–3), inert gases such as nitrogen and in negative pressure. FlowFit is suitable for a variety of applications, including technical building systems,

Title: VULC W701 MECHNICAL U BEND            38
Description: This Durapipe Vulcathene W70 38 x 38mm U-bend is made of virgin-grade polypropylene. Combined with other standard fittings, this bend can make up P, S and running traps. For P and S configurations, a length of Vulcathene mechanical pipe and a W15 coupler is added to one end, enabling connection to the waste fitting. The addition of a W29 loose nut sweep bend converts the bend into a P trap and with a further W29 creates an S trap. Meanwhile, connecting a W29 to each end of the U bend creates a running trap.

Description: Designed, manufactured and assembled in the UK, this JG Speedfit 22 x 15mm three-port stem manifold allows for the centralisation of service pipework at a single point. Developed with the input of the plumbers who will use it, the innovative FlowFit system ensures always-right installation, for a simpler job on-site with no need for deburring and calibration when cutting to length and the ability to laterally press and rotate for convenient and reliable pressing in difficult spots with no risk of contortion. This system is compatible with both cold and hot potable water, cooling and heating water with or without antifreeze agent and with service water and process water. It can also be used in treated water, rainwater with a pH value of <gt/>6, seawater and extinguishing water (wet, wet/dry or dry). It is also suitable for chemicals and technical liquids, compressed air (oil purity class 0–3), inert gases such as nitrogen and in negative pressure. FlowFit is suitable for a variety of applications, including technical building systems,
